On 25.3.1885 the part in Norfolk  became 
    part of the parish of Redenhall with Harleston, so that thereafter Mendham was 
    entirely in Suffolk. See also Table 2, notes (b) and (c).

Abolished 25.3.1885 and divided between the parishes of Metfield, 
    Mendham and Linstead Parva. See also Table 2, note (a).
